  "text": "gether with deeper AZM macromolecules would be in a pair of bands bilateral to the docked vesicles, as in mouse. At junctions where the relationship of the double row of membrane macromolecules to docked vesicles is unilateral, as at the junctions on the tonic muscle fibers of the lizard, the arrangement of the AZM relative to docked vesicles would be in a single band unilateral to docked vesicles, as in frog. Whether or not AZM contains structures identical to the beams, ribs, and pegs at the many other synaptic types throughout vertebrate and invertebrate nervous systems, where the arrangement of membrane macromolecules and docked vesicles is not linear and positioning of AZM relative to docked vesicles is more complex than at NMJs [CITATION_1] Waldrond et al., 1993; [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , it is reasonable to expect, based on similarities in active zone function, that in general AZM will have an orderly arrangement of macromolecules that link it to calcium channels in the presynaptic membrane and to docked vesicles.",
